.SH "NAME"
modbus_write_bits \- write many bits
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBint modbus_write_bits(modbus_t *\fR\fB\fIctx\fR\fR\fB, int \fR\fB\fIaddr\fR\fR\fB, int \fR\fB\fInb\fR\fR\fB, const uint8_t *\fR\fB\fIsrc\fR\fR\fB);\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBmodbus_write_bits()\fR function shall write the status of the \fInb\fR bits (coils) from \fIsrc\fR at the address \fIaddr\fR of the remote device\&. The \fIsrc\fR array must contains bytes set to TRUE or FALSE\&.
.sp
The function uses the Modbus function code 0x0F (force multiple coils)\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
The function shall return the number of written bits if successful\&. Otherwise it shall return \-1 and set errno\&.
.SH "ERRORS"
.PP
\fBEMBMDATA\fR
.RS 4
Writing too many bits
.RE
